## BUB Agent Usage

Three bounded read-only BUB agents were started:

- BUB-01 - Global `.instructions` inventory.
- BUB-02 - Core/Documentation reference inspection.
- BUB-03 - versioning strategy analysis.

BUB-01, BUB-02, and BUB-03 returned before final validation and were incorporated.

All BUB agents were instructed to avoid edits, git writes, repo restructuring, builds, tests, installs, services, secrets, and runtime execution.

## Source-of-Truth Policy Summary

Created `.instructions/GLOBAL_DOCS_SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md`.

Policy summary:

- Global `.instructions` owns portfolio coordination, maturity framework, request/sprint/task taxonomy, cross-nucleus blockers, and roadmap allocation.
- Nucleus `.instructions` owns local implementation constraints, validation commands, status, safety boundaries, and local workflow.
- Core owns ecosystem coordination semantics, federation principles, architectural boundaries, and registry/source-of-truth concepts.
- Documentation nucleus owns docs tooling, publishing standards, and quality processes.
- AxodusAPP docs own frontend integration-shell and visibility boundaries.
- Runtime/product behavior is not defined by global docs unless explicitly linked to a product nucleus.

Conflict rule:

- Latest coordinator-approved request, stricter safety boundary, stricter nucleus docs, Core semantics, Documentation tooling, and latest report evidence are checked in order. Unresolved conflict becomes a blocker.
- Core Registry presence must not imply authorization, implementation, production approval, runtime activation, or policy approval.
- Documentation should maintain the canonical public documentation surface; sprint text and planning reports must not become official public facts without review/migration.

## Ownership Policy Summary

Created `.instructions/GLOBAL_DOCS_OWNERSHIP.md`.

Policy summary:

- Portfolio Coordinator owns portfolio direction, queue sequencing, maturity framework acceptance, and cross-nucleus conflict decisions.
- Documentation Coordinator maintains global `.instructions` structure and validation procedure.
- Nucleus Owner owns local nucleus constraints and status.
- Safety Reviewer reviews production/execution-sensitive changes.
- Agent Coder executes approved tasks and validates artifacts.

Coordinator approval is required for maturity changes, queue changes, safety boundary changes, execution permission changes, versioning/repository structure changes, and production-ready claims.

## Versioning Options Summary

Created `.instructions/GLOBAL_DOCS_VERSIONING_STRATEGY.md`.

| Option | Summary | Recommendation |
|---|---|---|
| A | Keep global docs local-only | Temporary only |
| B | Dedicated Axodus Documentation/Governance repo | Preferred for clean portfolio governance |
| C | Move global docs under Core or Documentation repo | Acceptable if ownership boundaries are explicit |
| D | Convert `/opt/Axodus` root into Git repo | Not recommended by default |

Recommended option:

Option B, or Option C using the existing Documentation repo if no new repo should be created.

Additional guidance:

- Avoid placing global portfolio operations under Core unless the content is strictly architecture/source-of-truth vocabulary.
- Avoid using the existing Governance product repo as the global docs home by default because Governance is a product/domain nucleus and remains under HOLD/backlog control.

Decision status:

DECISION REQUIRED - NOT EXECUTED.

No Git migration, root initialization, or file move was performed.

